{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context\nThe identity epic shipped the merge-gate as `.github/workflows/verify-identity.yaml`, which walks\nthe MERGED LOG and grandfathers via `ENFORCE_SINCE` (CLI `rebar verify-identity`,\n`src/rebar/_commands/verify_authorship.py`). This story adds a **required-environment op-cert\nverification lane** that reuses that merged-log walk + grandfathering rather than standing up a\nparallel walker.\n\n**Op-cert storage shape (defined here; consumed by ee0b producer + 8f1d migration).** An op-cert\nis stored on a ticket in the `attestations` map under its kind (`plan-review` /\n`completion-verifier`) as a record carrying a **DSSE `envelope`** (`{payload, payloadType,\nsignatures:[{keyid, sig}]}`) — the asymmetric variant of today's HMAC record — plus the bound\n`{ticket_id, material_fingerprint, merged_log_commit}` fields needed to call\n`trusted_env.verify_required_environment`. This story only READS that shape (a fixture synthesizes\none); ee0b's trusted server and 8f1d's migration PRODUCE it.\n\n**Scope = verify-side + grandfathered.** Because producers (ee0b/8f1d) land later, the lane is\n**advisory until `ENFORCE_SINCE`** covers op-cert-bearing commits — exactly the identity gate's\ntransition mechanism — so adding it does not flip the repo to blocking before op-certs exist.\n\n**Grandfathering the ABSENCE case (the missing-op-cert enforcement anchor).** The identity gate's\n`_is_enforced(commit_sha, since_ref)` tests the commit that introduced *an event*. A ticket that\ncarries NO op-cert has no such event/commit. Resolution: the enforcement anchor for a ticket\nlacking a required-environment op-cert is the commit that introduced the ticket's **terminal\n`STATUS` event** — the status-change event whose target status is `closed` (rebar has no separate\n\"CLOSE\" event type; closure is a `STATUS` event, per `_store/event_append.py`). That event's\nintroducing commit is resolved with the same `authorship.resolve_event_commit` mechanism the\nidentity gate uses, then fed to `_is_enforced`: a ticket whose close-`STATUS` event predates\n`ENFORCE_SINCE` is grandfathered (advisory pass); one after it is enforced, so a missing/foreign\nop-cert fails. A ticket with no close-`STATUS` event yet (not closed) is out of scope for the\ncompletion-verifier lane.\n\n**Per-ticket walk.** `verify_authorship.py`'s merged-log helpers (`_collect_all`/`_collect_range`,\n`_ScopedEvent`) yield per-EVENT; op-cert enforcement is per-TICKET. `verify-opcert` reuses those\nhelpers to enumerate the in-scope event set, then **groups by `ticket_id`** and evaluates each\nticket once (its op-cert attestation + its close-`STATUS` anchor), rather than re-implementing the\nwalk.\n\n**Edit targets.** `src/rebar/_commands/verify_opcert.py` (new CLI, mirroring `verify_authorship.py`);\n`src/rebar/_cli/__init__.py` (add a `verify-opcert` equality-test intercept arm alongside the\nexisting `verify-identity`/`verify-commit-ticket` arms); `.github/workflows/verify-identity.yaml`\n(add the op-cert step + the CI-trigger audit comment).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A CLI entrypoint `rebar verify-opcert` (in `src/rebar/_commands/`, mirroring\n      `verify_authorship.py`) accepts `--require-environment <env_id>` (default from\n      `verify.require_environment` config) and `--since <ref>` (grandfathering), walks the merged\n      log's tickets (reusing the merged-log walk helper `verify_authorship.py` uses), and for each\n      in-scope ticket verifies its required-kind op-cert via\n      `rebar.attest.trusted_env.verify_required_environment` against `.rebar/trusted_environments.yaml`.\n      Exit 1 iff an ENFORCED in-scope ticket lacks a valid required-environment op-cert; else exit 0\n      (advisory). A unit test asserts the exit-code contract.\n- [ ] `.github/workflows/verify-identity.yaml` gains an op-cert verification **step** (same job /\n      same merged-log walk + `ENFORCE_SINCE`, NOT a parallel job) invoking `rebar verify-opcert`.\n      A test/assertion confirms the workflow file references `verify-opcert` and reuses the shared\n      `ENFORCE_SINCE` var.\n- [ ] A fixture test proves the gate: a ticket carrying a valid op-cert (DSSE envelope signed by a\n      test env key pinned in a fixture `.rebar/trusted_environments.yaml`) PASSES; a ticket\n      missing the op-cert, and a ticket whose op-cert is signed by a foreign (non-pinned) key,\n      both FAIL. Fixture location: `tests/interfaces/lifecycle/` (integration) or\n      `tests/unit/test_verify_opcert.py`; the test names the command it runs.\n- [ ] CI-trigger audit as a concrete artifact: a comment block in\n      `.github/workflows/verify-identity.yaml` enumerates its `on:` triggers and classifies each\n      INCLUDED (op-cert lane runs under it) or NO_FILTER (no `paths`/`branches` filter excludes an\n      op-cert-bearing change); a test asserts the audit comment is present and lists every trigger."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783981368928149001,"uuid":"8512744c-cbcd-4363-9b9a-c9b0cc4ad2d4"}